rådgivning</P></TI_TEXT></ML_TI_DOC></ML_TITLES><ML_AA_NAMES><AA_NAME LG="EN">Bergen Kommune</AA_NAME></ML_AA_NAMES></TRANSLATION_SECTION><FORM_SECTION><F02_2014 CATEGORY="ORIGINAL" FORM="F02" LG="EN"><LEGAL_BASIS VALUE="32014L0024"/><CONTRACTING_BODY><ADDRESS_CONTRACTING_BODY><OFFICIALNAME>Bergen Kommune</OFFICIALNAME><NATIONALID>964338531</NATIONALID><ADDRESS>Serviceboks 7880</ADDRESS><TOWN>Bergen</TOWN><POSTAL_CODE>5020</POSTAL_CODE><COUNTRY VALUE="NO"/><CONTACT_POINT>Johanne Jensen Vikeså</CONTACT_POINT><E_MAIL>johanne.vikesa@bergen.kommune.no</E_MAIL><n2016:NUTS CODE="NO"/><URL_GENERAL>https://permalink.mercell.com/111585793.aspx</URL_GENERAL><URL_BUYER>https://www.bergen.kommune.no/</URL_BUYER></ADDRESS_CONTRACTING_BODY><DOCUMENT_FULL/><URL_DOCUMENT>https://permalink.mercell.com/111585793.aspx</URL_DOCUMENT><ADDRESS_FURTHER_INFO_IDEM/><URL_PARTICIPATION>https://permalink.mercell.com/111585793.aspx</URL_PARTICIPATION><CA_TYPE VALUE="REGIONAL_AUTHORITY"/><CA_ACTIVITY VALUE="GENERAL_PUBLIC_SERVICES"/></CONTRACTING_BODY><OBJECT_CONTRACT><TITLE><P>EEA 051-2019 Procurement of geology Services</P></TITLE><REFERENCE_NUMBER>2019/70886</REFERENCE_NUMBER><CPV_MAIN><CPV_CODE CODE="71351220"/></CPV_MAIN><TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/><SHORT_DESCR><P>Bergen Municipality, c/o the Agency for Urban Environment, is responsible for the management, operation and maintenance of all municipal roads in Bergen. From time to time we get notifications of landslides, rock falls, or notes of concern from the public. The Agency for Urban Environment would first like to examine the situation with internal resources. In cases where we are uncertain or where we would like to get the situation clarified, there will be a need for a geologist who can assess the situation.</P></SHORT_DESCR><VAL_ESTIMATED_TOTAL CURRENCY="NOK">6000000.00</VAL_ESTIMATED_TOTAL><NO_LOT_DIVISION/><OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1"><CPV_ADDITIONAL><CPV_CODE CODE="71351913"/></CPV_ADDITIONAL><CPV_ADDITIONAL><CPV_CODE CODE="71351910"/></CPV_ADDITIONAL><CPV_ADDITIONAL><CPV_CODE CODE="71351730"/></CPV_ADDITIONAL><n2016:NUTS CODE="NO051"/><SHORT_DESCR><P>Bergen Municipality, c/o the Agency for Urban Environment, would like to enter into a contract with a geologist in order to examine situations in both acute/ad hoc and planned events.</P><P>Acute/ad hoc events:</P><P>Acute events can, for example, be:</P><P>— to assess whether municipal roads ought to be closed for traffic,</P><P>— to assess whether an existing situation is safe,</P><P>— to assess whether residents ought to be evacuated.</P><P>Turn-outs for acute events can occur on any day and at all times of the day/night. The maximum response time must not be more than 2 hours from when the Agency for Urban Environment makes contact. An engineering geologist must be provided, or equivalent with minimum 10 years experience.</P><P>We would like a prepared report after the first assessment.</P><P>Planned events:</P><P>Bergen Municipality, c/o the Agency for Urban Environment, needs assessments in cases where there is not an acute need for a geologist. In these cases we would like a prepared report with recommended measures.</P><P>Technical follow-up in the field.</P><P>This involves guidance and follow-up of contractors working on protection assignments.</P></SHORT_DESCR><AC><AC_PRICE/></AC><VAL_OBJECT CURRENCY="NOK">6000000.00</VAL_OBJECT><DURATION TYPE="MONTH">24</DURATION><RENEWAL/><RENEWAL_DESCR><P>The contract will be valid for 2 years, with an option for the contracting authority to extend the contract for up to a further 2 years, to a maximum of 4 years.</P><P>The contracting authority can choose to extend the contract multiple times, for e.g. for 1 year at a time.</P></RENEWAL_DESCR><NO_ACCEPTED_VARIANTS/><NO_OPTIONS/><NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/></OBJECT_DESCR></OBJECT_CONTRACT><LEFTI/><PROCEDURE><PT_OPEN/><FRAMEWORK><SINGLE_OPERATOR/></FRAMEWORK><NO_CONTRACT_COVERED_GPA/><DATE_RECEIPT_TENDERS>2019-10-15</DATE_RECEIPT_TENDERS><TIME_RECEIPT_TE